        <body>
            <head>
                <title>The Schuyler Sisters</title>
            </head>
            <div type="song">

                <sp who="#burr">
                    <speaker>BURR</speaker>
                    <l>There’s nothing rich folks love more</l>
                    <l>Than going downtown and slummin’ it with the poor</l>
                    <l>They pull up in their carriages and gawk</l>
                    <l>At the students in the common</l>
                    <l>Just to watch them talk</l>
                    <l><seg type="#fact">Take <persName ref="#philipS">Philip Schuyler</persName>: the man is
                        loaded</seg></l>
                    <l>Uh-oh, but little does he know that</l>
                    <l><seg type="#fiction">His daughters, <persName ref="#peggy">Peggy</persName>, <persName ref="#angelica">Angelica</persName>, <persName ref="#eliza">Eliza</persName></seg></l>
                    <l>Sneak into the city just to watch all the guys at—</l>
                </sp>

                <sp who="#company">
                    <speaker>COMPANY</speaker>
                    <l>Work, work!</l>
                </sp>

                <sp who="#angelica">
                    <speaker>ANGELICA</speaker>
                    <l><persName ref="#angelica">Angelica</persName>!</l>
                </sp>

                <sp who="#company">
                    <speaker>COMPANY</speaker>
                    <l>Work, work!</l>
                </sp>

                <sp who="#eliza">
                    <speaker>ELIZA</speaker>
